# Jackknife — Cursor IDE Rules

## Project Overview
Dual-purpose Python toolkit: importable "blades" library + project scaffold CLI.
Python 3.12, Poetry, FastAPI (optional), Streamlit (default frontend).

## CRITICAL: Python Commands
- ALWAYS: `poetry run python`, `poetry run pytest`, `poetry run jackknife`
- NEVER: `python3`, `pip install`, direct python invocations

## CRITICAL: Branch Workflow
```bash
git checkout -b fix/name      # bug fixes
git checkout -b feature/name  # new blades or features
git checkout -b chore/name    # config, deps, CI updates
# NEVER commit directly to main
```

## Architecture
Each blade lives in `jackknife/blades/<name>/` with:
- `base.py`    — Protocol (structural typing) + ABC (enforced inheritance)
- `models.py`  — Pydantic models for all I/O
- `factory.py` — `create_X(settings)` factory function
- `__init__.py` — public API exports

Core utilities in `jackknife/core/`:
- `config.py`     — pydantic-settings; `get_settings()` cached with lru_cache
- `exceptions.py` — JackknifeError hierarchy
- `logging.py`    — structlog; use `get_logger(__name__)`
- `models.py`     — JackknifeBaseModel, TimestampedModel, IdentifiedModel

## Code Standards
- Line length: 100 characters (ruff enforced)
- Type annotations required on all public functions
- Files must stay under 200 lines
- `extra="forbid"` on all Pydantic models (fail fast on typos)
- `async def` everywhere in blade interfaces

## Configuration Rules
- `jackknife.toml` — non-secret config (committed)
- `.env` — secrets only (NEVER committed, NEVER relative paths)
- ALL paths must be absolute — pydantic validator enforces this

## Testing
- `pytest` with `asyncio_mode = "auto"` (no @pytest.mark.asyncio needed)
- Tests mirror source: `tests/blades/test_memory/` → `jackknife/blades/memory/`
- Coverage minimum: 80% (CI fails below this)

## Conventional Commits
feat: | fix: | docs: | refactor: | test: | ci: | chore:
